In this file we describe how you can use the following metaheuristic implementations:

a) pbig (Population-Based Iterated Greedy Algorithm (PBIG)) for the WID problem   (*)

b) cmsa-pbig-wid-v (Construct, Merge, Solve & Adapt (CMSA) integrated with PBIG) for WID problem (**)

(*)(**) Described in the paper “The Weighted Independent Domination Problem: Integer Linear Programming Models and Metaheuristic Approaches" by P. Pinacho, C. Blum and J.A. Lozano (submitted to EJOR)

PBIG:
 usage: ./pbig -i <input_graph> [options]
     options:
            -t 	   float       	  Set the execution time limit in seconds [default: 1000.0]
            -lperc float          Set the lower bound as percentage  [default: 30.0 (30%)].
            -uperc float          Set the upper bound as percentage [default: 30.0 (30%)].
            -drate float          Set the determinism rate of the probabilistic greedy [default: 0.5 (50%) ]. 
            -lsize int            Set the size of the candidate list for the probabilistic greedy [default: 10].
            -psize int            Set the population size [default: 10].


CMSA-PBIG-WID-V:

 usage: ./cmsa-pbig-wid-v -i <input_graph> [options]
        ./cmsa-pbig-wid-v -help
    options:
            -drate_feeder    int     Set the determinism rate of the probabilistic greedy for CMSA [default: 0.5 (50%) ].    
            -lsize_feeder    int     Set the size of the candidate list of the probabilistic greedy for CMSA [default: 1].
            -maxage    	     int     Set the maximum age for nodes in C' for CMSA [default: 10].
            -sols    	     int     Number of solutions generated by greedy per iteration of CMSA [default: 1]
            -t       	     float   Total admissible running time for CMSA in seconds [default: 3600.0]
            -drate_pbig      float   Set the determinism rate of the probabilistic greedy for the PBIG component [default: 0.5 (50%) ]. 
            -lsize_pbig      int     Set the size of candidate list of probabilistic greedy for the PBIG component [default: 10].
            -psize_pbig      int     Set the population size of the PBIG component [default: 10].
            -time_pbig       float   Set the execution time limit in seconds for the PBIG component [default: 100.0]
            -D_l_pbig        float   Set the lower bound as percentage for the PBIG component [default: 30.0 (30%)].
            -D_u_pbig        float   Set the upper bound as percentage for the PBIG component [default: 30.0 (30%)].
            -greedy_selector [0|1]   Select one of the two greedy implementations available [default: 1]
            

